Part I - (Prosper Loan Data Exploration)¶

by (Sobia Arshad) Introduction:

This dataset is a financial daatset which is related to Loans,borrowers,Lenders interest rates etc.Prosper is a california based company which specialises in loans with a low interest rate to the borroweres.In this dataset, we are using the data from the Posper to analyse it and trying to find the pattern in the Prosper data and communicate our data findings through Data exploration.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

In this dataset we have a total of 113,937 loans with 81 attributes/columns for them most of which are float and values objects.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

APR is a simple percentage term used to express the numerical amount paid by an individual or entity yearly for the privilege of borrowing money.

I am mostly interested in predicting what features are best for predicting cost of credit as a yearly rate which is Borrowers Annual percentage Rate(APR) for the loan?

Does Term affects APR?

Is APR higher than Interest rate?

Another thing that can be explored for this Loan system is how monthlyIncome of a person effects his loan amount.If he is earning more than Is HE/SHE able to apply for more loan amount?

We will also see that how ProsperRating is affecting other variables of interest in this loan system

There are so many attributes in this dataset but for data analysis and exploration purpose I will take into account few main features which are as follows:

Term: The length of the loan expressed in months. LoanStatus: BorrowerRate 'ProsperRating (Alpha)', 'ListingCategory (numeric)', 'EmploymentStatus', 'StatedMonthlyIncome', 'TotalProsperLoans', 'LoanOriginalAmount', 'LoanOriginationDate', 'Recommendations', 'Investors'

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Loan amount can have an impact on determing APR so we have to take it into account during our data exploration phases. Monthly income will also be explored during this exploration and will see its effects too. Also Prosper rating will be taken into account. Loanstatus is of prime importance in this dataset as it has values like(Cancelled,charged off,Completetd,Current,defaulted,final payement in progress,pastDue)which shows as if how many loans were approved and who many were cancelled. Another important attribute is 'Term' which specifies the length of loan given by this company 'Prosper'. The Borrower's interest rate for this loan(BorrowerRate)is also of significant importance in this dataset. In our analysis we will also consider how Loan Amount will effect staus of Loan to be approved.

Before starting our Exploration we would like to take sample of the data with attributes that we are considering in this anlysis.

Univariate Exploration¶

Borrower APR(The Borrower's Annual percentage Rate)¶

Annual Percentage Rate (APR) is the cost of credit as a yearly rate. The APR is a disclosure mandated by the Truth in Lending Act of 1968. It is designed to accurately disclose the true cost of credit and provide a standard basis of comparison for the costs of credit.

I will start looking at the variable of main interest here which is Borrowers APR.Let us visualise it by Histogram and see the results:

In [16]:
n, bins, patches = plt.hist(data = chosen_loandata, x = 'BorrowerAPR',  bins='auto', color='#0504aa', 
                            alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
plt.xlabel('Borrower APR')
plt.ylabel('Frequency of Loans')
plt.title('Histogram Distribution of Borrower APR')
Out[16]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Histogram Distribution of Borrower APR')

Analysis:

In the above figure choosing bins=auto gives a good representation of data and by looking at the above histogram we can see that it seems to be multimodial distribution as it has multiple peaks.It shows tha quite a large number of loans have APR 0.35 to 0.36(35% to 36%) also very few loans have APR greater than 0.45.we can also verify through following code:

bbox_props = dict(boxstyle="square,pad=0.3", fc="w", ec="k", lw=0.72)
kw = dict(arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="-"),
          bbox=bbox_props, zorder=0, va="center")

for i, p in enumerate(wedges):
    ang = (p.theta2 - p.theta1)/2. + p.theta1
    y = np.sin(np.deg2rad(ang))
    x = np.cos(np.deg2rad(ang))
    horizontalalignment = {-1: "right", 1: "left"}[int(np.sign(x))]
    connectionstyle = "angle,angleA=0,angleB={}".format(ang)
    kw["arrowprops"].update({"connectionstyle": connectionstyle})
    ax.annotate(recipe[i], xy=(x, y), xytext=(1.35*np.sign(x), 1.4*y),
                horizontalalignment=horizontalalignment, **kw)

ax.set_title("Matplotlib LoanStatus: A donut")

plt.show()

Analysis:

The above Donut shows that the status of mostly Loans is Current which merans that they are currently ongoing.

Multivariate Exploration¶

We would like to investigate here that how categorical variables are related to Borrower APR and Loan original amount.

First of all we should have a clear understanding of Prosper Rating in this system:

Every loan request is assigned a Prosper Rating through our proprietary rating system, which allows us to maintain consistency in our evaluation. The Prosper Rating is expressed as a letter grade that indicates the expected level of risk associated with a loan listing. Each letter grade corresponds to an estimated average annualized loss rate range.
